text.p: These are some of the leading stories in the official Iraqi press on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.
- Russia appreciates Iraq's call for Kurdish factions to come to Baghdad for peace talks.
- Arab health ministers urge the U.N. to allow Iraq to transport the sick by planes. (Iraq is under an air embargo since its 1990 invasion of Kuwait).
- A group of Egyptian businessmen arrive in Baghdad to hold trade fair from Saturday.
- Education minister discusses with French charge d'affaires in Baghdad means of enhancing cooperation.
(The above stories were also carried by THAWRA)
